    • Python Tuple Methods are:
        # count() -> It returns the number of occurrences of the specified value.
        # index() -> It returns the index of the first occurrence of the specified value.
        # len() -> It returns the number of items in a tuple.
        # min() -> It returns the smallest item in a tuple.
        # max() -> It returns the largest item in a tuple.
        # sum() -> It returns the sum of all items in a tuple.
        # sorted() -> It returns a new sorted list from the items in a tuple.
        # any() -> It returns True if any item in the tuple is true. If the tuple is empty, it returns False.
        # all() -> It returns True if all items in the tuple are true. If the tuple is empty, it returns True.
        # del() -> It deletes the tuple completely.

