# 9_Docstring_and_pep-8
    1. what is Docstring and why we use it ?
    -> A docstring is a documentation string in Python. It is written inside triple quotes at the beginning of a function, class, or module to explain its purpose. We use it to make code easier to understand and maintain. It can also be viewed using help() or __doc__.
    
    2. what is PEP-8 ?
    -> PEP-8 => Python Enhancement Proposal. PEP (Python Enhancement Proposal) is a proposal that describes improvements, new features, or standards for Python. 

